column2: for when you have one Object
tagged by some Excel Type Code such as 4 Bool, 1 Int or Float, 16 Exception, 64 List, or 2 Str
(and probably not tagged by the poorly doc'ed Excel Type Codes of 0, 8, 32, and 128)

column5: # Excel raises CalcError to block lists of zero items
# Excel collapses lists of one item
# Bool of lists of >= 2 items would be always True

=LAMBDA(obj,
        SWITCH(TYPE(obj),
            1, int.repr(obj),
            2, str.repr(obj),
            4, bool.repr(obj),
            64, list.repr(obj),
            128, function.repr(obj),
            "<" & obj & ">"
))
=shuffled sort uniq of items or chars
